The Kerala Financial Corporation (KFC) and Kitco have signed a memorandum of understanding for promoting innovation and entrepreneurship development in the State.As per the MoU, Kitco will send commercially viable and technologically matured start-ups to KFC for securing financial assistance. It will also recommend start-ups incubated at Kitco and other agencies for KFC funding after imparting adequate training and mentoring. Joy Oommen, chairman and managing director of KFC, and Cyriac Davies, managing director, Kitco, were the signatories to the MoU.â€” Special Correspondent